{{Multiple issues|{{external links|date=October 2012}}{{Orphan|date=October 2012}}}} '''Commercial Advancement Training Scheme (CATS)''' is a dual education system adopted from the German Dual System and introduced in [[Namibia]] in 2005, and [[South Africa]] in 1985. It combines [[apprenticeship]]s in a company and technical education at a University in one course.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.manica.com.na/news/n5.htm |title=Expo broadens students' opportunities |publisher=Manica.com.na |date= |accessdate=2012-10-13 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130219050021/http://www.manica.com.na/news/n5.htm |archive-date=2013-02-19 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> It is accepted and recognized by the [[European Union]] through the German Chamber of Commerce and Industry. The programme is also accredited by the [[South African Qualifications Authority]] (SAQA) evaluation level 5 /NQF level 5.{{citation needed|date=October 2012}}
==Namibia== Introduced in 2005 in Namibia, classes are offered by the Centre for Enterprise Development (CED)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polytechnic.edu.na/news_index/newsdocs/2011/september/ced%20responds%20to%20development%20challenges.pdf|title=CED responds to development challenges – Deputy Minister|publisher=Polytechnic.edu.na|accessdate=2012-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140703001807/http://polytechnic.edu.na/news_index/newsdocs/2011/september/ced%20responds%20to%20development%20challenges.pdf|archive-date=2014-07-03|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> at the [[Polytechnic of Namibia]] and practical training is provided by partner companies such as Manica, [[Namport]], Agra, [[TransNamib]], Wesbank Transport, Cymot and others.
==South Africa== The system was introduced in [[South Africa]] in 1985, thereafter graduating more than 1,600 students in the two countries, with the contribution of 360 companies and institutions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://suedafrika.ahk.de/service/ausbildung/cats/ |title=CATS |publisher=Suedafrika.ahk.de |date= |accessdate=2012-10-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111013124206/http://suedafrika.ahk.de/service/ausbildung/cats/ |archivedate=2011-10-13 |df= }}</ref>
==Advantages of dual education== The student works as an employee of the company from the beginning and receives tasks according to his growing abilities. Companies who employ the student after his education, the company gets a well-trained employee. The student develops both hard and soft skills. The student develops under real conditions, getting an earlier look at what the work entails, earning money in the process.
