The Annual Workshop on '''Formal Approaches to Slavic Linguistics''' (often abbreviated '''FASL''') is one of the most reputable international [[academic conference]]s in the field of [[formal linguistics|formal]] [[Slavic linguistics]]. Each meeting is hosted by a [[List of American institutions of higher education|United States]] or [[List of universities in Canada|Canada]] university in May; the [[proceedings]] are published in the next year by [[Michigan Slavic Publishers]] of [[University of Michigan]] in [[Ann Arbor, MI]].
