{{Infobox Convention | name = Windycon | image = | caption = | status = Active | genre = Science fiction/Fantasy | venue = | location = Lombard, Illinois | country = United States | first = 1974 | last = | organizer = ISFiC | filing = Non-profit | attendance = ''circa'' 1,300-1,500 | website = http://www.windycon.org/ }}
'''Windycon''' is a [[science fiction convention]] held in [[Lombard, Illinois]], on the weekend closest to [[Veterans Day (United States)|Veterans Day]].
[[ISFiC]], the parent corporation that runs Windycon,<ref name="pavlac">Pavlac, Ross, [http://www.isfic.org/WhatIs.asp What's an ISFiC], ISFiC Web Site, retrieved, 2015-11-10</ref> was founded in 1973 in Chicago. The first Windycon was held the following year and has been held annually ever since either in Chicago or a Chicago suburb.<ref>[http://www.isfic.org/conspast.asp The Windycon Big List], Windycon Web Site, retrieved, 2007-05-19</ref> It is a general interest convention.
ISFiC and Windycon were founded to raise the profile of fandom in Chicago in preparation for a [[Worldcon]] bid.<ref name="pavlac"/> In 1982, Chicon IV was the result. From its small beginnings, Windycon has grown to have an annual membership hovering around 1300. It is the largest of the two fan-run Chicago conventions.
Annually since 1986, ISFiC has hosted a writers contest, open to unpublished authors. The contest is judged by professional authors and editors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.isfic.org/Winners.asp|title=ISFiC, Inc.: Writers Contest Winners|website=www.isfic.org|accessdate=15 September 2018}}</ref> Separately, Windycon has hosted a writers' workshop under the coordination of [[Richard Chwedyk]] since 2000.<ref>{{Citation | last = Foster | first = Adrienne | title = Next Manuscript, Please: Amazing Tales of the Worldcon Writers Workshop | newspaper = SFWA Bulletin | pages = 10 | date = August–September 2009 | accessdate = 2009-09-29}}</ref>
In addition to traditional con activities, Windycon has also run a series of on-line chats during the con, hosting by Cybling.<ref>Murphy, Janice, [http://cybling.hypermart.net/windycon/index.html Windycon 26 Chats], Cybling, retrieved, 2007-05-19</ref><ref>Murphy, Janice, [http://www.cybling.com/conventions/windyconxxix/chats.html Windycon 29 Chats], Cybling, retrieved, 2007-05-19</ref>
